Manchester United on Saturday evening dropped two points after failing to beat Watford in a Premier League tie. Man United drew 0-0 against Watford at Old Trafford after failing to score against the visitors. Ralf Rangnick’s side had 22 shots against Watford’s 10 shots during the encounter. The result means Man United still maintains the 4th position on the Premier League table with 47 points from 24 games. The Red Devils are two points ahead of fifth-place Arsenal, who have three games in hand. Man United will now face Man City in their next game on March 6. Meanwhile, Man City, Liverpool and Chelsea occupied the first, second and third positions on the log.